The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks for vehicle detection using polarised long wave infrared (LWIR) sensors. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) applications, as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the use of LWIR sensors falls under the category of infrared imaging (cs.IR).
